lenders.name: Dean
lenders.loan_because: "Pay It Forward" - a child’s philosophy that the world would be a better place if everyone tried to "pay it forward" by helping a stranger, and by that stranger in turn helping another.  Based on a novel by Catherine Ryan Hyde, the movie "Pay It Forward" is about a boy named Trevor McKinney (Haley Joel Osment) who is inspired by his social studies teacher Mr. Simonet (Kevin Spacey) and comes up with a school project based on a simple concept: everyone should do something good for three people and ask them to "pay it forward" instead of pay it back. The basic concept of the movie’s title can be applied to my kiva.org account, affording me the opportunity to make a difference in the world by doing a good deed.  Can individuals really make a difference in these troubled times? The power of a simple act of kindness can change the world in the most beautiful, gentle way.  Just think back to when you were little and to the things you remember most of your childhood.  Chances are you will have the clearest memories of the kindness someone extended to you.  Those are the memories I hold in my heart as treasures in my life.  Those simple acts of love and compassion have helped me through some subsequent terrible moments in my life.  They have lifted my spirits in ways no material possession could.  Do your part to make the world a better place. Get involved.  Pay it forward.
